events.description: The Siege of Baghdad ends with the surrender of the last Abbasid caliph to Hulegu Khan, a prince of the Mongol Empire.
events.html: • 1258 – The Siege of Baghdad ends with the surrender of the last Abbasid caliph to Hulegu Khan, a prince of the Mongol Empire.[1]

events.description: In front of the high altar of Greyfriars Church in Dumfries, Robert the Bruce murders John Comyn, sparking the revolution in the Wars of Scottish Independence.
events.html: • 1306 – In front of the high altar of Greyfriars Church in Dumfries, Robert the Bruce murders John Comyn, sparking the revolution in the Wars of Scottish Independence.

events.description: The St Scholastica Day riot breaks out in Oxford, England, leaving 63 scholars and perhaps 30 locals dead in two days.
events.html: • 1355 – The St Scholastica Day riot breaks out in Oxford, England, leaving 63 scholars and perhaps 30 locals dead in two days.[2]

events.description: Vasco da Gama sets sail from Lisbon, Portugal, on his second voyage to India.
events.html: • 1502 – Vasco da Gama sets sail from Lisbon, Portugal, on his second voyage to India.[3]

events.description: Lord Darnley, second husband of Mary, Queen of Scots, is found strangled following an explosion at the Kirk o' Field house in Edinburgh, Scotland, a suspected assassination.
events.html: • 1567 – Lord Darnley, second husband of Mary, Queen of Scots, is found strangled following an explosion at the Kirk o' Field house in Edinburgh, Scotland, a suspected assassination.

events.description: Huilliches in Chiloé rebel against Spanish encomenderos.
events.html: • 1712 – Huilliches in Chiloé rebel against Spanish encomenderos.[4]

events.description: French and Indian War: The Treaty of Paris ends the war and France cedes Quebec to Great Britain.
events.html: • 1763 – French and Indian War: The Treaty of Paris ends the war and France cedes Quebec to Great Britain.[5]

events.description: Napoleonic Wars: The Battle of Champaubert ends in French victory over the Russians and the Prussians.
events.html: • 1814 – Napoleonic Wars: The Battle of Champaubert ends in French victory over the Russians and the Prussians.

events.description: Queen Victoria of the United Kingdom marries Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha.
events.html: • 1840 – Queen Victoria of the United Kingdom marries Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha.

events.description: First Anglo-Sikh War: Battle of Sobraon: British defeat Sikhs in the final battle of the war.
events.html: • 1846 – First Anglo-Sikh War: Battle of Sobraon: British defeat Sikhs in the final battle of the war.

events.description: Jefferson Davis is notified by telegraph that he has been chosen as provisional President of the Confederate States of America.
events.html: • 1861 – Jefferson Davis is notified by telegraph that he has been chosen as provisional President of the Confederate States of America.

entities.name: President of the Confederate States of America

events.description: American Civil War: A Union naval flotilla destroys the bulk of the Confederate Mosquito Fleet in the Battle of Elizabeth City on the Pasquotank River in North Carolina.
events.html: • 1862 – American Civil War: A Union naval flotilla destroys the bulk of the Confederate Mosquito Fleet in the Battle of Elizabeth City on the Pasquotank River in North Carolina.

events.description: HMS Dreadnought, the first of a revolutionary new breed of battleships, is christened.
events.html: • 1906 – HMS Dreadnought, the first of a revolutionary new breed of battleships, is christened.[6]

events.description: Józef Haller de Hallenburg performs the symbolic wedding of Poland to the sea, celebrating restitution of Polish access to open sea.
events.html: • 1920 – Józef Haller de Hallenburg performs the symbolic wedding of Poland to the sea, celebrating restitution of Polish access to open sea.

events.description: About 75% of the population in Zone I votes to join Denmark in the 1920 Schleswig plebiscites.
events.html: • 1920 – About 75% of the population in Zone I votes to join Denmark in the 1920 Schleswig plebiscites.

events.description: Texas Tech University is founded as Texas Technological College in Lubbock, Texas.
events.html: • 1923 – Texas Tech University is founded as Texas Technological College in Lubbock, Texas.

events.description: The Việt Nam Quốc Dân Đảng launches the failed Yên Bái mutiny in hope of overthrowing French protectorate over Vietnam.
events.html: • 1930 – The Việt Nam Quốc Dân Đảng launches the failed Yên Bái mutiny in hope of overthrowing French protectorate over Vietnam.

events.description: In round 13 of a boxing match at New York City's Madison Square Garden, Primo Carnera knocks out Ernie Schaaf. Schaaf dies four days later.
events.html: • 1933 – In round 13 of a boxing match at New York City's Madison Square Garden, Primo Carnera knocks out Ernie Schaaf. Schaaf dies four days later.

events.description: Second Italo-Abyssinian War: Italian troops launch the Battle of Amba Aradam against Ethiopian defenders.
events.html: • 1936 – Second Italo-Abyssinian War: Italian troops launch the Battle of Amba Aradam against Ethiopian defenders.

events.description: Spanish Civil War: The Nationalists conclude their conquest of Catalonia and seal the border with France.
events.html: • 1939 – Spanish Civil War: The Nationalists conclude their conquest of Catalonia and seal the border with France.

events.description: The Soviet Union begins mass deportations of Polish citizens from occupied eastern Poland to Siberia.
events.html: • 1940 – The Soviet Union begins mass deportations of Polish citizens from occupied eastern Poland to Siberia.

entities.name: Territories of Poland annexed by the Soviet Union

events.description: World War II: Attempting to completely lift the Siege of Leningrad, the Soviet Red Army engages German troops and Spanish volunteers in the Battle of Krasny Bor.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: Attempting to completely lift the Siege of Leningrad, the Soviet Red Army engages German troops and Spanish volunteers in the Battle of Krasny Bor.

events.description: The Paris Peace Treaties are signed by Italy, Romania, Hungary, Bulgaria, Finland and the Allies of World War II.
events.html: • 1947 – The Paris Peace Treaties are signed by Italy, Romania, Hungary, Bulgaria, Finland and the Allies of World War II.

events.description: U.S. President Dwight D. Eisenhower warns against United States intervention in Vietnam.
events.html: • 1954 – U.S. President Dwight D. Eisenhower warns against United States intervention in Vietnam.

events.description: Cold War: Captured American U2 spy-plane pilot Gary Powers is exchanged for captured Soviet spy Rudolf Abel.
events.html: • 1962 – Cold War: Captured American U2 spy-plane pilot Gary Powers is exchanged for captured Soviet spy Rudolf Abel.

events.description: Melbourne–Voyager collision: The aircraft carrier HMAS Melbourne collides with and sinks the destroyer HMAS Voyager off the south coast of New South Wales, Australia, killing 82.
events.html: • 1964 – Melbourne–Voyager collision: The aircraft carrier HMAS Melbourne collides with and sinks the destroyer HMAS Voyager off the south coast of New South Wales, Australia, killing 82.

events.description: The 25th Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified.
events.html: • 1967 – The 25th Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified.

entities.name: Twenty-fifth Amendment to the United States Constitution

events.description: Ras Al Khaimah joins the United Arab Emirates, now making up seven emirates.
events.html: • 1972 – Ras Al Khaimah joins the United Arab Emirates, now making up seven emirates.

events.description: Kenyan soldiers kill an estimated 5,000 ethnic Somali Kenyans in the Wagalla massacre.
events.html: • 1984 – Kenyan soldiers kill an estimated 5,000 ethnic Somali Kenyans in the Wagalla massacre.

events.description: Ron Brown is elected chairman of the Democratic National Committee, becoming the first African American to lead a major American political party.
events.html: • 1989 – Ron Brown is elected chairman of the Democratic National Committee, becoming the first African American to lead a major American political party.

events.description: IBM supercomputer Deep Blue defeats Garry Kasparov in chess for the first time.
events.html: • 1996 – IBM supercomputer Deep Blue defeats Garry Kasparov in chess for the first time.

events.description: France and Belgium break the NATO procedure of silent approval concerning the timing of protective measures for Turkey in case of a possible war with Iraq.
events.html: • 2003 – France and Belgium break the NATO procedure of silent approval concerning the timing of protective measures for Turkey in case of a possible war with Iraq.

events.description: Forty-three people are killed and three are injured when a Fokker 50 crashes near Sharjah International Airport.
events.html: • 2004 – Forty-three people are killed and three are injured when a Fokker 50 crashes near Sharjah International Airport.[7]

events.description: The communications satellites Iridium 33 and Kosmos 2251 collide in orbit, destroying both.
events.html: • 2009 – The communications satellites Iridium 33 and Kosmos 2251 collide in orbit, destroying both.

events.description: Thirty-six people are killed and 39 others are injured in a stampede in Allahabad, India, during the Kumbh Mela festival.
events.html: • 2013 – Thirty-six people are killed and 39 others are injured in a stampede in Allahabad, India, during the Kumbh Mela festival.

events.description: South Korea decides to stop the operation of the Kaesong joint industrial complex with North Korea in response to the launch of Kwangmyŏngsŏng-4.
events.html: • 2016 – South Korea decides to stop the operation of the Kaesong joint industrial complex with North Korea in response to the launch of Kwangmyŏngsŏng-4.

events.description: Nineteen people are killed and 66 injured when a Kowloon Motor Bus double decker on route 872 in Hong Kong overturns.
events.html: • 2018 – Nineteen people are killed and 66 injured when a Kowloon Motor Bus double decker on route 872 in Hong Kong overturns.

events.description: The traditional Carnival in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil is canceled for the first time because of the COVID-19 pandemic.
events.html: • 2021 – The traditional Carnival in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil is canceled for the first time because of the COVID-19 pandemic.[8]

events.description: Texas' worst energy infrastructure failure, the 2021 Texas power crisis, starts.
events.html: • 2021 – Texas' worst energy infrastructure failure, the 2021 Texas power crisis, starts.[9]
